The blooming water of the red tide spans about 130 miles of coastline from the northern district of Pinellas to the southern district of Lee.
Spots were observed about 10 miles off the coast in Hillsborough County, but last week there were relatively fewer spots.
The red tide was also observed in the Pasco district.
In the Hillsborough district, low to high concentrations were observed in the high seas, the lowest to high concentrations in the Manatee district, the lowest to high concentrations in the low seas, the lowest to high concentrations in the low seas, the lowest to high concentrations in the low seas, the highest concentrations in the low seas, the highest concentrations in the low seas, the highest concentrations in the low seas and the low seas.
Respiratory irritation continues to occur in the districts of Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Lee and Collier.
Respiratory tract irritation was not reported in northwest Florida last week.
